The Catalog lists all academic policies and procedures. It includes information on fees, curriculum requirements and four-year courses of study for all of the University’s undergraduate majors, descriptions of both graduate and undergraduate course offerings, and a listing of faculty members. Every effort has been made to make the Catalog accurate as of the date of publication; however, the Catalog does not constitute a contractual commitment that the university will offer all the courses or programs as described.

Raggio Education Building, the Nazir Anasari Business Building, the Fitzgerald Student Services Building, and the E.L. Wiegand Fitness Center.

To do whatever it takes. To follow every lead. To go to the ends of the earth in pursuit of knowledge. This is what drives the University of Nevada, Reno – and it is this spirit that has powered our rise to Carnegie® Classification R1, joining America’s top research universities.

As a land-grant institution, we emphasize making a college education a realizable goal for those who apply.
You can afford a Nevada education.
Did you know more than 50% of our students graduate with no debt?

Are you planning your college experience? Refer to our cost estimates tables to get a better understanding of your expected tuition and fees as an undergraduate student at the University of Nevada, Reno.
Considering graduate school? Learn more about our tuition and fees for graduate students at the University of Nevada, Reno.
If you've got the grades to go to the University of Nevada, Reno, family finances shouldn't stand in your way.
That's why there's The Nevada Guarantee. If you're a Nevada resident and come from a low-income family, we'll guarantee you
, plus all the academic and social support you'll need to graduate in four years or less.
If you're a new freshman or transfer student from the Western U.S., you can save on your out-of-state tuition.

We are a proud participant in WUE, which allows students from participating states and territories to pay only 150% of our standard Nevada resident tuition. Participating areas include Alaska, Arizona, California, Colorado, Commonwealth of the Northern Marianas Islands, Guam, Hawaii, Idaho, Montana, New Mexico, North Dakota, Oregon, South Dakota, Utah, Washington and Wyoming.

Known as one of America's best small cities, Reno is a burgeoning tech hub that offers an array of year-round activities.
At the University of Nevada, Reno, history meets innovation. Traditional red-brick buildings from the 1800s sit alongside 21st-century cutting-edge research facilities.
The University of Nevada, Reno is a member of the Mountain West Conference with six men's sports teams and ten women's sports teams.

For today’s students and tomorrow’s professionals to be competitive, we’re developing the talent and technologies required by global, knowledge-intensive industries. These efforts will impact people around the world, prepare skilled workers, develop the next generation of leaders and expand economic growth across Nevada and beyond.
